###git cheatsheet###

for pushing and pulling repos:

git status				shows status  
git add <file>			selects file to be added
git commit -m ""		commits single files on staging area
git commit -u ""		commits all files on staging area
git push origin master	push files

git status				shows status
git fetch				fetches from one or more repositories
git pull				updates local files

to update from fork to local repo:

git remote -v
git add upstream [url]
git rebase upstream/master
...then git push that mother
###if done for the first time###
git push -f origin master
